This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing and machine learning, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses multi-agent learning environments and methods, which could place it in the cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) sub-category. The use of machine learning and statistical patterns also suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) could be a relevant sub-category. The emergence of non-verbal communication could potentially place the paper in the cs.SD (Sound) sub-category, although this is less likely. Finally, the paper's focus on language and communication could also make it relevant to the cs.LG (Learning) sub-category.
